obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34478)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34478&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] This Act may be called the Destructive Insects and Pests Act, 1914.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^3***.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 1 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 3 and the Schedule, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 3 and the Schedule, ibid.`
  line
  line `33. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f 1-11-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34468)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34468&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "crops" includes all agricultural or horticultural crops ^1[and all trees, bushes or plants];`
  line
  line `(b) "import" means the bringing or taking by sea, ^2[land or air] ^3[across any customs frontier as defined`
  line `by the Central Government]; ^4***`
  line
  line `(c) "infection" means infection by any insect, fungus or other pest injurious to a crop; ^5***`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1938, s. 3, for "and trees or bushes".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1930, s. 2, for "or land".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the A.O. 1937. For definition of customs frontier, see section 3A of the Sea Customs Act, 1878 (8 of 1878) and Gazette of`
  line `India, Pt. II, Sec. 3, dated 6th August, 1955, p. 1521.`
  line
  line `4. The word "and" omitted by Act 3 of 1939, s. 2.`
  line
  line `5. The word "and" omitted by the A.O. 1948, which was earlier added by Act 3 of 1939, s. 2.`
  line
  line `6. Clause (d) omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-11-1956). Earlier it was subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34469)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of Central Government to regulate or prohibit the import of articles likely to infect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34469&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, prohibit or regulate, subject to such`
  line `restrictions and conditions as it may impose, the import into ^1[India], or any part thereof, or any specified`
  line `place therein, of any article or class of articles likely to cause infection to any crop ^2[or of insects generally`
  line `or any class of insects].`
  line
  line `(2) A notification under this section may specify any article or class of articles ^2[or any insect or class of`
  line `insects], either generally or in any particular manner, whether with reference to the country of origin or the`
  line `route by which imported or otherwise.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) The Central Government may, by notification under this section, also levy and collect such fees at`
  line `such rates and in such manner as may be specified therein for making an application for a permit to import, or`
  line `for making inspection, fumigation, disinfection, disinfestation or supervision of, any article or class of articles`
  line `of any insect or class of insects under this section].`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and "the Schedule for the said territories".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 6 of 1938, s. 4.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 12 of 1992, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27-10-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34470)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Operation of notification under section 3.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34470&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A notification under section 3 shall operate as if it had`
  line `been issued under section 19 of the Sea Customs Act, 1878 (8 of 1878), and the officers of Customs at every`
  line `port shall have the same powers in respect of any article with regard to the importation of which such a`
  line `notification has been issued as they have for the time being in respect of any article the importation of which`
  line `is regulated, restricted or prohibited by the law relating to Sea Customs, and the law for the time being in`
  line `force relating to Sea Customs or any such article shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (34480)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Central Government to regulate or prohibit transport from State to State`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34480&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Power of Central Government to regulate or prohibit transport from State to State of insects`
  line `or articles likely to infect.--The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, prohibit`
  line `or regulate, subject to such conditions as the Central Government may impose, the export from a State or the`
  line `transport from one State to another State ^2*** of any article or class of articles likely to cause infection to any`
  line `crop or of insects generally or any class of insects.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1938, s. 5.`
  line
  line `2. The words "in British India" rep. by the A.O. 1948.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_b:
  sectionId (34472)
  sectionNo 4B
  orderNo 6
  title `Refusal to carry article of which transport is prohibited.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1938, s. 5.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34472&sectionno=4B&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[. Refusal to carry article of which transport is prohibited--When a notification has been issued`
  line `under section 4A, then, notwithstanding any other law for the time being in force, the person responsible for`
  line `the booking of goods or parcels at any railway station or inland steam vessel station,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the notification prohibits export or transport, shall refuse to receive for carriage at, or to`
  line `forward or knowingly allow to be carried on, the railway or inland steam vessel from that station`
  line `anything, of which import or transport is prohibited, consigned to any place in a State other than the State`
  line `in which such station is situate; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the notification imposes conditions upon export or transport shall so refuse, unless the`
  line `consignor produces, or the thing consigned is accompanied by, a document or documents of the`
  line `prescribed nature showing that those conditions are satisfied.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_c:
  sectionId (34473)
  sectionNo 4C
  orderNo 7
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1938, s. 5.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34473&sectionno=4C&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_4_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[4C. [Application of section 4B to articles exported to the State of Jammu and Kashmir.] Omitted by the`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir (Extension of Laws) Act, 1956 (62 of 1956), s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_d:
  sectionId (34474)
  sectionNo 4D
  orderNo 8
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34474&sectionno=4D&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_4_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[4D. Power of Central Government to make rules.--^2[(1)] The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules prescribing the nature of the documents which shall`
  line `accompany any article or insect the export or transport whereof is subject to conditions imposed under`
  line `section 4A, or, which shall be held by the consignor or consignee thereof, the authorities which may issue`
  line `such documents and the manner in which the documents shall be employed:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have`
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that`
  line rule.]
obj_root_law_sections_4_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1938, s. 5.`
  line
  line `2. Section 4D re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso omitted by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34475)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34475&sectionno=5&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may ^1[, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette,] ^2`
  line `*** make rules for the detention, inspection, disinfection or destruction ^3[of any insect or`
  line `class of insects or] of any article or class of articles in respect of which a notification has been issued under`
  line `section 3 ^3[or under section 4A] or of any article which may have been in contact or proximity thereto, and`
  line `for regulating the powers and duties of the officers whom it may appoint in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) In making any rule under this section the State Government may direct that a breach thereof shall be`
  line `punishable with fine, which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `2. The words "subject to the control of the G.G. in C." were omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 6 of 1938, s. 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (34476)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 10
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34476&sectionno=5A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Penalties.--Any person who knowingly exports any article or insect from a State or transports any`
  line `article or insect from one State to another 5^2*** in contravention of a notification issued under section 4A, or`
  line `attempts so to export or transport any article or insect ^3*** and any person responsible for the booking of`
  line `goods or parcels at a railway or inland steam vessel station who knowingly contravenes the provisions of`
  line `section 4B shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred and fifty rupees and, upon any`
  line `subsequent conviction, with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. The words "in British India" were omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line
  line `3. The words "or exports or attempts to export from India to the State of Jammu and Kashmir any article or insect in respect of which`
  line `a notification under section 4C has been issued," omitted by Act 62 of 1956 s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34477)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 11
  title `Protection to persons acting under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238&sectionId=34477&sectionno=6&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00008_191402_1523342057238
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against any person for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
